- your title has "unicorn blood sacrfice" (not mad crawl)<br>- instructions on first screen is v helpful<br>- messages appear at the top AND the bottom. V confusing. Suggest you drop the one at the bottom and just fill the log at the top.<br>- graphics is awesome<br>- the 'confused' effect where keys become random is a great mechanic<br>- I can see friends and enemies through walls when I 'display' tags. Intentional?<br>- equipping things is a bit unintuitive. I got it after clicking around a bit.<br>- suggest the heart beat is turned off when health is 100%<br>- using a wand of flames requires no less than four mouse clicks. At least the 2nd click can be removed.<br>- i realised there was no line of sight with the wand until after I'd committed to an attack. I couldn't see a way to cancel the attack. (suggest right-click to cancel wand).<br>- I got stuck on some stairs and had to quit the game. That sames stairs worked on at least 3 previous occasions (I went up/down a few times) but then got stuck the 4th time. Screen shot for what it's worth.<br><br>I think the game is really engaging. Much more improved once I realised I had to follow my party. I even stopped my other background game to focus on this one.  <img class="smilies" src="https://love2d.org/forums/images/smilies/ms-smile.png" width="16" height="16" alt=":)" title="Smile">  I wanted to explore more and see what else I can pick up and whack something on the head with my club.  <img class="smilies" src="https://love2d.org/forums/images/smilies/ms-smile.png" width="16" height="16" alt=":)" title="Smile"><br><br>I played the exe version (not that that matters).<dl class="file"><dt class="attach-image"><a href="https://love2d.org/forums/download/file.php?id=24128&amp;mode=view"><img src="https://love2d.org/forums/download/file.php?id=24128" class="postimage" alt="Untitled.jpg" /></a></dt></dl><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=170436">togFox</a> 